<subSubSection id="977BCEF1EDC2621AABA4236E18C2B669" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" type="notes">
<paragraph id="7EA61FED0181E459637EAFE93E9AD372" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3DDA522E91CF32AB7532E7DD4B5F0CC6" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">
<taxonomicName id="C7216A5F30372972D09543725EFD28C6" authorityName="F. A. Wolf, J. Agric. Res., Washington 33 (7): 625" authorityYear="1926" baseAuthorityName="H. S. Fawc." class="Ascomycetes" family="Diaporthaceae" genus="Diaporthe" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Diaporthe citri" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="citri">
<emphasis id="4CFBCE7DAB041B920B2040B1FE9D62D6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Diaporthe citri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a widely distributed species in citrus-growing regions. In the present study, four isolates (CFCC 53079, CFCC 53080, CFCC 53081 and CFCC 53082) from symptomatic leaves of 
<taxonomicName id="85A958986E878BA87BAFC3EF63C78855" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Diaporthaceae" genus="Citrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Citrus sinensis" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="sinensis">
<emphasis id="8B3F1382DBD15774E36679A63645C45B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">Citrus sinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were congruent with 
<taxonomicName id="9237C2D5DCE2D96112C8F90EC3844147" genus="D." lsidName="D. citri" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" rank="species" species="citri">
<emphasis id="237B1EA03E05DC5CC9310033D3D8417F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">D. citri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on DNA sequence and morphological data (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="00D2A28DAA494EC7FDA52896055735C9" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Phylogram of Diaporthe from a Maximum Likelihood analysis based on combined ITS, cal, his 3, tef 1 and tub 2. Values above the branches indicate Maximum Likelihood bootstrap (left, ML BP ≥ 50 %) and Bayesian probabilities (right, BI PP ≥ 0.90). The tree is rooted with Diaporthella corylina. Strains in current study are in blue font and the ex-type cultures are in bold font." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.77.59999.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/497460" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">1</figureCitation>
). The clade was, therefore, confirmed to be 
<taxonomicName id="E3B21D098F7602FC641F59EA2D6F494F" genus="D." lsidName="D. citri" pageId="0" pageNumber="41" rank="species" species="citri">
<emphasis id="F00E2C6E7F56DAC96A97FE4DC1C14AB5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="41">D. citri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
